The paper deals with object detection in autonomous vehicles using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on the use of geometric constraints and physical world information, which are important aspects of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep learning techniques also suggests a possible fit with machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the filtering of false detections, which is a common problem in natural language processing (cs.CL).
